<SLUG> BC-BBN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WRIGLEY'S BOZOS GUILTY, TOO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ If Chad ``Freddy'' Kreuter finds himself suspended
this week, so what.
</P>
<P>
   If Rick ``Jack'' Dempsey gets pulled into Frank Robinson's
dragnet, fine.
</P>
<P>
   But if any of those ever-lovin'-losin', Harry
Caray-derriere-kissin', Second City psychos who infest Wrigley
Field manage to skirt punishment for luring the Dodgers bullpen
into the stands to join their AA meeting last week, that'd be
baseball's cruelest punishment.
</P>
<P>
   Listen, a Dodgers cap costs about 20 bucks at the trinket stand.
You don't need to whack a visiting team member over the head to get
one, even if all your cash for the week has already been spent on
some of Mrs. O'Leary's private stock.
</P>
<P>
   Be thankful Kreuter didn't choke the livin' daytime baseball out
of all you Windy City winos. If Reggie Smith was still the Dodgers
bench coach, none of you'd be around today to worry about missing
last call 'cause you'd be with St. Harry putting your mouth under
the spigot right about now.
</P>
<P>
   Warning to that poor racist John Rocker: When you get to
Chitown, don't expect that L.A.-friendly moon-shot reception. The
only friendly confines these fans should be invited to need bars
over the windows instead of on the concourse, along with a 9 p.m.
lock down. ...
</P>
<P>
   -The question isn't which hat Rickey Henderson will end up
wearing on his Hall of Fame plaque. It's whether he'll have worn
one for every team in existence before he gets there. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Kobe Bryant wants to come up with a rap song for his new bride,
but he can't think of a rhyme for ``prenup''. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Magic Johnson's next project: Opening fitness centers in the
inner-city area. Calling 'em ``Magic Clubs''. ...
</P>
<P>
   -The Clippers can do a lot with the No.3 pick. All three UCLA
players should still be on the board. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Last time the Fox network sent a sports chick over to Egypt to
start prying open pyramids, Suzy Kolber's career was cursed.
</P>
<P>
   Hope the same doesn't happen to Lisa Guerrero, who joins Hugh
Downs at an excavation site in the middle of the desert for Fox's
latest tomb raid special (Tuesday, 8 p.m.). ...
</P>
<P>
   -Finally, in all seriousness ...
</P>
<P>
   It was easy to be sorta skeptical watching former Dodger Steve
Garvey, writer Dick Schaap and one-time L.A. Raider Steve Beuerlein
on C-SPAN last week, testifying before a Capitol Hill Senate
appropriations subcommittee on whether funding needed to be
extended for finding a cure for Lou Gehrig's Disease.
</P>
<P>
   Celebs standing up before politicians on TV trying to raise
money for their pet causes can look suspicious. And Sen. Arlen
Specter addressed that fact.
</P>
<P>
   When Beuerlein brought up before the panel his friend, Jeff
Scherer, a former football player at Long Beach State who in a very
short time has watched his body ravaged by the disease to where he
can't even speak for himself, there was no reason to doubt his
sincerity.
</P>
<P>
   Garvey then responded to Specter: There are many who criticize
and few who act. I challenge those who question our motives to look
into this and do something about it.
</P>
<P>
   Amen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
