<P>
   (UNDATED) _ He's something of a hybrid Superman: a
Brazilian-Frenchman who now runs Japan's beleaguered,
second-largest car company, Nissan. Carlos Ghosn used to be the
chief operating officer at Renault, France's biggest car company,
where he made his considerable reputation as ``le cost cutter.''
Indeed, Ghosn paved the way for Renault's dramatic turnaround after
he arrived there from the Michelin tire company. Now he must
perform the same, badly needed magic at Nissan. &QL;
