<SLUG> BC-TECH-GEAR0523-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    That purring sound is coming from your PC
 &HT;    By Shaun Conlin
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Keep your home computer spiffed up and running
on all cylinders with Iolo Technologies' System Mechanic 3.2
(Shareware/30 days free, $20-$60; www.iolo.com, for Windows PCs). A
cadre of 12 powerful tools, this utility will optimize your PC's
Internet and network speed and security settings, remove invalid,
orphaned, obsolete and nonsense files, then find and fix broken
shortcuts. Also included is an easy-to-understand start-up manager,
a safe installation feature that tells you exactly what's been
altered after new programs are added, and even an incinerator as a
companion to the recycle bin for total obliteration of sensitive
files. System Mechanic did somehow allow this particular
click-happy user to lose track of his word processor, but for the
most part the cleaning machine is idiot friendly if not idiot
proof. The free and fully functioning 30-day-demo enticement is the
real kicker here. Try it out. As those holistic folks like to say,
there's nothing like a good purge to keep you spiffed.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
