federal law designed to shield children from accidental exposure to
erotic cable programs that their parents have not chosen to
receive. In a 5-4 decision, which is a victory for Playboy
Enterprises Inc., the court agrees with the firm that the law was
too broad and violated the First Amendment rights of cable TV
viewers to receive explicit programs. By MARK HELM.
