&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tetris for tots
 &HT;    By Shaun Conlin
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   The classic, all consuming, highly addictive Tetris has been
reworked and specifically revamped for preschoolers as Kids Tetris
($30; www. hasbro-interactive. com; for the PC). Still utilizing
the familiar falling multi-gonal block shapes, Kids Tetris has
those traditional, ``elaborate'' puzzle pieces pre-fastened to form
more rudimentary block shapes that fall at a leisurely pace. More
importantly, the blocks are animated with happy cartoon faces that
actually talk to the player, giving hints, suggestions and joyful
words of encouragement. Fun, funny and rewarding gameplay, while
still offering elemental lessons in problem solving and motor
skills.
</P>
