<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`SLEEPY HOLLOW' A NODDER; `CARNIVAL OF SOULS' SOARS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Sleepy Hollow'' _ Director Tim Burton and star
Johnny Depp worked together in ``Ed Wood'' to create a contemporary
masterpiece. But masterpieces don't happen often _ especially in
the movies _ and Burton and Depp's adaptation of Washington
Irving's legendary story falls short. Despite marvelous special
effects and a solid performance from Depp, the film lacks dramatic
construction. If Burton spent as much time creating character depth
as he did weaving the effects, ``Sleepy Hollow'' might have
achieved more than a few frights in the night.
</P>
<P>
   DVD PICK OF THE WEEK: ``Carnival of Souls'' _ Herk Harvey, an
industrial filmmaker, had the idea of making a movie about a church
organist who's haunted by things after a nasty car wreck. And
that's all he had. He did not have good actors. He had no money to
speak of. And he had to shoot the whole movie on less than a
shoestring. So why is this black-and-white, low-budget B movie so
creepy? Through a marvelous restoration and excellent supplementary
material _ including very smart and informative liner notes _ this
two-disc set is a prime example of how limitations can be
transformed into assets. The odd camera angles, out-of-synch sound,
and various other ``mistakes'' only lend a terrifying credibility
to the proceedings. It was Harvey's only feature. At $39.95, it's a
bit pricey to own, but well worth renting.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 30: ``Snow Falling on Cedars'' (DVD),
``Miss Julie,'' ``Man on the Moon'' (DVD), ``Divided We Stand,''
``The 20th Century'' (10 volumes; DVD). June 6: ``Girl,
Interrupted'' (DVD), ``Mr. Death: The Rise and Fall of Fred A.
Leuchter, Jr.'' (DVD), ``Backlash,'' ``Kiss the Sky'' (DVD), ``A
Scandal in Paris,'' ``On Our Merry Way'' (DVD), ``Andy Kaufman
Plays Carnegie Hall.'' June 13: ``The Green Mile'' (DVD), ``Leila''
(DVD), ``The Emperor and the Assassin'' (DVD), ``Desperately
Seeking Susan'' (DVD), ``The Third Miracle'' (DVD), ``Light It
Up.'' June 20: ``Anna and the King,'' ``Topsy-Turvy'' (DVD),
``Liberty Heights'' (DVD). July 11: ``All About My Mother'' (DVD),
``Jaws'' (DVD). July 18: ``What Planet Are You From?'' (DVD),
``Angela's Ashes.'' July 25: ``Magnolia'' (DVD), ``The Beach.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
