Kosovo said Monday. His comments came as American peacekeepers
reported a 10-year-old boy was killed, and two other children were
seriously wounded on Sunday by a cluster bomb in an unmarked site
in southern Kosovo. Over 100 people have died, and hundreds more
have been injured, in mine and bomb accidents since refugees
returned to Kosovo last June when NATO forces moved in. By Carlotta
Gall.
