auditoriums, a club-size jazz cafe, two rehearsal studios and a
classroom, all wired for recording, broadcast and Webcast. In its
new spaces the organization intends to present jazz 365 days a
year, with its larger rooms also available for opera, dance and the
Lincoln Center Festival. By Jon Pareles.
