<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BORDER-SHOOTING-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BORDER PATROL AGENT KILLS UNDOCUMENTED IMMIGRANT 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By JAMES PINKERTON 
c.2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARLINGEN, Texas _ FBI agents Monday were investigating the
fatal shooting of a young Mexican immigrant by a Border Patrol
agent during a struggle on the banks of the Rio Grande.
</P>
<P>
   A Border Patrol surveillance unit using night-vision equipment
spotted a group of apparently four people crossing the shallow
river east of Brownsville, Texas, at 5 a.m. Sunday and radioed for
backup, said spokesman Ramiro De Anda.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant Border Patrol Chief Harry Beall said one of the agents
who responded got into a scuffle with an undocumented immigrant
after he found him hiding in some brush and attempted to detain
him.
</P>
<P>
   During the struggle, the Mexican national wrestled the agent's
baton away from him. The officer, believing the man intended to
grab his gun, drew his semi-automatic pistol and fired twice, Beall
said. The immigrant was shot once in his upper chest, Beall added.
</P>
<P>
   The 25-year-old man was taken to a hospital in Brownsville,
where he died around 8 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   ``Evidently, he was determined not to be taken into custody and
he was willing to fight for the officer's weapon to prevent it,''
said Beall. ``The officer feared for his life and unfortunately had
to resort to deadly force.''
</P>
<P>
   Two other immigrants in the group were detained and a fourth
escaped.
</P>
<P>
   Officials declined to identify the agent involved in the
shooting, but said he was a 32-year-old native Texan who has been
on duty more than two years.
</P>
<P>
   Beall said the shooting victim's companions said he was a
Mexican citizen from the state of Quintana Roo, in the Yucatan
peninsula.
</P>
<P>
   In a statement released Monday, the Mexican consulate in
Brownsville said: ``Incidents like this hurt and damage the
relationship between Mexico and the United States and threaten the
harmony of residents on both sides of the border.''
</P>
<P>
   On March 19, a Border Patrol agent detaining a group of
immigrants near the riverside community of Santa Rosa, Texas, shot
an undocumented immigrant who allegedly pulled a pistol on the
officer. The immigrant, who was shot in the arm, is jailed on
charges of assaulting a federal officer. The agent has returned to
duty.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday's shooting was the latest in a series of shootings of
undocumented immigrants near the border, including the May 13
killing of a Mexican youth by a 75-year-old rancher outside
Brackettville, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
