 &UR; MONEYBAG (Q&AMP;A COLUMN) _ &LR;  Q: How is it possible that Kmart Corp.,
with $36 billion in annual revenues, has a market capitalization of
less than $4 billion? Does this really represent all the
outstanding shares, or are there a lot of other shares held by
company insiders?  &UR; COLUMN BY ARTHUR M. LOUIS &LR;
